        "title": "fix(plugin): harden schema and metadata fuzz boundaries",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- hardens plugin-owned schema and metadata boundaries found during fuzzing with synthetic `fuzzplugin` / `mockplugin` fixtures\n- latest refresh hardens plugin inspect/status registry-entry summaries: typed hook, custom hook, tool, diagnostic, and memory-provider registry reads are now bounded so one malformed plugin entry cannot crash plugin inspection\n- keeps the draft PR branch updated as work continues; current head is `0256ac70dcc589f86e55d9b7251e30e9f7fa9fad`, proven on `origin/main` at `b352cb2d8e7f25a582f06ffe234fdc5229cb49f2`\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check src/plugins/inspect-shape.ts src/plugins/status.ts src/plugins/status.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD -- src/plugins/inspect-shape.ts src/plugins/status.ts src/plugins/status.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-oxlint.mjs src/plugins/inspect-shape.ts src/plugins/status.ts src/plugins/status.test.ts`\n- `CI=1 node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run src/plugins/status.test.ts --reporter=verbose`: 1 file passed, 29 tests passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local`: clean on the plugin inspect/status registry-entry summary slice\n- scrubbed touched files/spec/PR body for the reported plugin name and private local paths\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: plugin-owned schema, metadata, command metadata, hook registration, tool registration options, CLI registration options, bundled agent tool result middleware options, captured middleware options, captured capability id surfaces, memory embedding provider registration, runtime embedding adapter merge/direct lookup, process-global embedding provider registry restore/list/register paths, migration provider runtime resolution, provider contract registry resolution, setup-only provider/backend runtime registration, compaction provider registration, capability provider runtime resolution, provider runtime hook lookup, shared provider resolver projection, active runtime CLI backend projection, provider discovery entry projection, explicit web provider public artifact projection, document/web-content extractor public artifact projection, trusted tool policy decision handling, Gateway Control UI descriptor projection, Gateway plugin session action dispatch, dynamic plugin session action method-scope resolution, plugin-registered Gateway method descriptor scope resolution, channel plugin Gateway method discovery, `tools.catalog` active registry metadata projection, plugin inspect/status Gateway method summaries, and plugin inspect/status registry-entry summaries no longer trust crashy getters, revoked proxies, mutable arrays/records, malformed runtime entries, malformed ids, unreadable aliases, unreadable hook aliases, unreadable labels/auth fields, unreadable backend configs, unreadable CLI commands, hostile callback metadata, throwing provider/extractor factories, unreadable public artifact metadata, throwing trusted policy evaluators, unreadable trusted policy decision fields, unreadable gateway descriptor metadata, unreadable session action metadata, malformed matched action scopes, unreadable gateway method descriptor names/scopes, unreadable channel gateway method arrays/elements, unreadable tool metadata entries, unreadable tool metadata records, unreadable deferred tool entries, unreadable deferred tool ownership fields, unreadable inspect Gateway method descriptor owners/names, or unreadable inspect typed hook/custom hook/tool/diagnostic/memory-provider registry fields while healthy sibling registrations continue where the surface is availability-oriented and security-sensitive policy/scope failures fail closed.\n\nReal environment tested: local linked OpenClaw worktree on the draft PR branch, rebased onto `origin/main` at `b352cb2d8e7f25a582f06ffe234fdc5229cb49f2`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: ran focused formatting, diff check, linting, Vitest, and autoreview commands listed in Verification after the plugin inspect/status registry-entry summary slice; after the final rebase, reran formatting, diff check, linting, and Vitest on the rebased head.\n\nEvidence after fix: `status.test.ts` now covers unreadable plugin inspect typed hook, custom hook, custom hook events, tool names, diagnostic message, and registry ownership fields while preserving healthy `mockplugin` typed hook, custom hook, tool, diagnostic, and legacy compatibility notice output.\n\nObserved result after fix: malformed active registry entries no longer crash plugin inspect/status shape calculation or inspect report output; unreadable malformed plugin-owned entries are skipped, custom hooks with unreadable event lists are not misreported as empty-event hooks, diagnostics are normalized before inspect output, and healthy sibling summaries still appear.\n\nWhat was not tested: broad Blacksmith/Testbox changed gate and AWS Crabbox broad gate were not rerun for this refresh; current proof is the targeted plugin inspect/status fuzz surface plus formatter/lint/autoreview checks.\n",
